Twenty people have been injured after two taxi&#8217;s collided in Johannesburg on Wolmerans and Rissik on Tuesday.Arrive Alive said: &#8220;Approximately 20 people were injured in the collision, sustaining injuries ranging from minor to serious. One seriously injured patient required Advanced Life Support intervention.&#8221;According to reports, one taxi turned in front of the other resulting in a T-bone collision, causing one to overturn.The patients were triaged and treated at the scene before being transported to various nearby facilities for further care.JMPD will further investigate the accident.-TNA Reporter